clnk - utility to create shortcuts in windows

Requirements:
  Put folder with vsvars***.bat scripts in your PATH (Visual Studio)
  Change variable INSTALLATION_FOLDER in clnk.bat to folder where you want to install all shortcuts

Usage:
  clnk (application_path) (shortcut_name) [startup_directory]
  Where:
    application_path - Path to application you want create shortcurt
    shortcut_name - Name of shortcut
    startup_directory - Optional - Startup folder for application

NOTE!
Dont delete .clnk folder and put it in the same folder with clnk.bat

Q: Why not using .lnk files?
A: .lnk files can't be runned from console